freenet.client
Class InsertException

java.lang.Object
  java.lang.Throwable
      java.lang.Exception
          freenet.client.InsertException
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class InsertException
extends Exception

Thrown when a high-level insert fails. For most failures, there will not be a stack trace, or it will be inaccurate.

See Also:

Field Detail

errorCodes

public FailureCodeTracker errorCodes
Collect errors when there are multiple failures. The error mode will be FATAL_ERRORS_IN_BLOCKS or TOO_MANY_RETRIES_IN_BLOCKS i.e. a splitfile failed.

uri

public FreenetURI uri
If a non-serious error, the URI we expect the insert to go to if it had succeeded.
